body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

 A JSZip is not a constructor error is thrown when attempting to generate and write an Excel workbook buffer using workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer(). This appears to be an issue with how ExcelJS resolves its internal JSZip dependency within the current build/bundler environment.

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript

export const GenerateExcelTemplate = async (worksheetsName : excelTemplateVal[] = []) => {
  try {
    const workbook: ExcelJS.Workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
    if(worksheetsName.length === 0) throw Error('Invalid Worksheet')

    worksheetsName.forEach((worksheet) => {
      const sheet = workbook.addWorksheet(worksheet.sheetName)
      const mappedColumns = new Map()
      sheet.getRow(1).font = { bold: true }
      for (const [index, colName] of worksheet.columns.entries()) {
        const letterVal = colNumberToLetter(index + 1)
        mappedColumns.set(colName, letterVal)
        sheet.getCell(`${letterVal}1`).value = colName || ''
        sheet.getColumn(letterVal).width = DEFAULT_WIDTH
      }

      worksheet.rows.forEach((item, index) => {
        const rowIndex = index + 2
        for (const key in item) {
          if (Object.hasOwn(item, key) && mappedColumns.has(key)) {
            const keyValue = mappedColumns.get(key)
            Object.assign(sheet.getCell(`${keyValue}${rowIndex}`), item[key])
          }
        }
      });
    })
    const buffer = await workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer();
    return buffer.toString('base64');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error)
    throw error
  }

```

